text: Gilbert Holmes (1772-1846) was a clergyman in the Church of IrelandBurke's Landed Gentry Of Ireland, 18122, Pg.334 during the late 18th century and the first four decades of the nineteenth."Handbook of British Chronology" By Fryde, E. Greenway, D.E;Porter, S; Roy, I: Cambridge, CUP, 1996 , 9780521563505 Holmes was educated at Trinity College, Dublin."Alumni Dublinenses : a register of the students, graduates, professors and provosts of Trinity College in the University of Dublin (1593-1860)Burtchaell,G.D/Sadlier,T.U p407: Dublin, Alex Thom and Co, 1935 He was Dean of Ardfert from 1802 to 1842“A New History of Ireland” Moody,T.W; Martin,F.X; Byrne,F.J;Cosgrove,A: Oxford, OUP, 1976 He died at Kilmore, County Tipperary"The Church of Ireland in County Kerry" Murphy, J.A. p243: Cork, Lulu, 2016 on 23 December 1846."Fasti Ecclesiae Hibernicae: The succession of the prelates Volume 1" Cotton,H. p445: Dublin, Hodges & Smith, 1848-1878 ==References== Category:Deans of Ardfert Category:Alumni of Trinity College Dublin Category:1772 births Category:1846 deaths
